description: List the available reports for a given profiling group and time range.

parameters.name: endTime
parameters.description: The end time of the profile to get analysis data about. You must specify startTime and endTime. This is specified using the ISO 8601 format. For example, 2020-06-01T13:15:02.001Z represents 1 millisecond past June 1, 2020 1:15:02 PM UTC.

parameters.name: nextToken
parameters.description: The nextToken value returned from a previous paginated ListFindingsReportsRequest request where maxResults was used and the results exceeded the value of that parameter. Pagination continues from the end of the previous results that returned the nextToken value.

parameters.name: profilingGroupName
parameters.description: The name of the profiling group from which to search for analysis data.

parameters.name: startTime
parameters.description: The start time of the profile to get analysis data about. You must specify startTime and endTime. This is specified using the ISO 8601 format. For example, 2020-06-01T13:15:02.001Z represents 1 millisecond past June 1, 2020 1:15:02 PM UTC.

nested_items.name: findingsReportSummaries
nested_items.description: The list of analysis results summaries.

nested_items.name: id
nested_items.description: The universally unique identifier (UUID) of the recommendation report.

nested_items.name: profileEndTime
nested_items.description: The end time of the period during which the metric is flagged as anomalous. This is specified using the ISO 8601 format. For example, 2020-06-01T13:15:02.001Z represents 1 millisecond past June 1, 2020 1:15:02 PM UTC.

nested_items.name: profileStartTime
nested_items.description: The start time of the profile the analysis data is about. This is specified using the ISO 8601 format. For example, 2020-06-01T13:15:02.001Z represents 1 millisecond past June 1, 2020 1:15:02 PM UTC.

nested_items.name: profilingGroupName
nested_items.description: The name of the profiling group that is associated with the analysis data.

nested_items.name: totalNumberOfFindings
nested_items.description: The total number of different recommendations that were found by the analysis.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: The nextToken value to include in a future ListFindingsReports request. When the results of a ListFindingsReports request exceed maxResults, this value can be used to retrieve the next page of results. This value is null when there are no more results to return.
